sentences: Tim Kingsbury (born 1977) is a Canadian musician and member of the indie rock band Arcade Fire.
Kingsbury began to play with Arcade Fire in 2003 after the break-up of the band's original membership.
Arcade Fire performed at Guelphâ€™s Hillside Festival in 2005, a performance Sam Baijal, artistic director of Hillside, credits with giving the Festival a huge boost in popularity.
Kingsbury also toured and recorded with Montreal band Wolf Parade as a bassist, appearing on the album the 2005 album Apologies to the Queen Mary.
In August 2015 he launched a side project under the name "Sam Patch" along with fellow Arcade Fire member Jeremy Gara and Toronto artist Basia Bulat.

Kingsbury recorded the song "In to Trouble" for the film 2020 film Pieces of a Woman, and in 2021 released the song as a digital single.
